{"id": "EUVD-2019-6118", "enisaUuid": "b1bc07d9-2ab1-35f5-b843-798a2cf88a03", "description": "In the Linux kernel through 5.2.14 on the powerpc platform, a local user can read vector registers of other users' processes via an interrupt. To exploit the venerability, a local user starts a transaction (via the hardware transactional memory instruction tbegin) and then accesses vector registers. At some point, the vector registers will be corrupted with the values from a different local Linux process, because MSR_TM_ACTIVE is misused in arch/powerpc/kernel/process.c.", "datePublished": "2019-09-13T12:45:49", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-05T00:34:53", "baseScore": 4.4, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:N/A:L", "references": ["https://www.suse.com/security/cve/CVE-2019-15031.html", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2020:1493", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2020:1372", "https://ubuntu.com/security/CVE-2019-15031", "https://linux.oracle.com/cve/CVE-2019-15031.html", "https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/commit/?id=a8318c13e79badb92bc6640704a64cc022a6eb97", "http://www.openwall.com/lists/oss-security/2019/09/10/4", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/4135-2/", "http://lists.opensuse.org/opensuse-security-announce/2019-09/msg00064.html", "http://lists.opensuse.org/opensuse-security-announce/2019-09/msg00066.html", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/4135-1/", "https://security.netapp.com/advisory/ntap-20191004-0001/"], "aliases": ["CVE-2019-15031"], "assigner": "mitre", "epss": 0.08, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "db2fd90f-9f42-3399-9c90-9b1f9751b38c", "product": {"name": "n/a"}, "product_version": "n/a"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "c5655a19-63cc-3887-a8af-0059db0048fd", "vendor": {"name": "n/a"}}], "isExploited": false}